1.0 	09 June 2000,	Simon Trimmer <simon@veritas.com>
	Initial release.
1.01	19 June 2000,	Simon Trimmer <simon@veritas.com>
	general tidy up and argument sequencing fix
	added default microcode filename and -u switch
1.02    29 June 2000,   Simon Trimmer <simon@veritas.com>
	fix from Richard Schaal <richard.schaal@intel.com>
	to be more flexible with the file formats.
	added a man page into section 8
1.03	07 Sept 2000,   Simon Trimmer <simon@veritas.com>
	a few small fixes from Tigran Aivazian <tigran@veritas.com>
	Makefile changes (abstraction for packaging and portability)
	more Makefile changes from Giacomo Catenazzi <cate@neper.ethz.ch>
	RPM .spec file
	integrate 2.2.16 backport from Andreas Steinmetz <ast@domdv.de>
	added Makefile device node creation (to be tested with devfs)
	added the quiet and very quiet options (-q and -Q)
	added a redhat style rc startup script
1.04	17 January 2001, Simon Trimmer <simon@veritas.com>
	startup script portability changes (tar, rpm and SuSE)
	build RPM direct from tar file (rpm -ta microcode_ctl-x.xx.tar.gz)
	readme tidyup
	replace P6 with IA32 - the Pentium 4 is of family 15
	new microcode release from intel
1.05	31 May 2001, Simon Trimmer <simon@veritas.com>
	new microcode release from Intel (01 May 2001 arrived this morning)
	Debian startup script fixes from Peter Kovacs <pkovacs@webmachines.com>
	added asm/cache.h to make compatible with Andrea Arcangeli's patches.
1.06	11 Jun 2001, Simon Trimmer <simon@veritas.com>
	deferred device install for devfs: Alan Eldridge <alane@geeksrus.net>
	Suse portability changes: Robb Romans <robb@austin.ibm.com>
	Slackware portability changes: Keven Belanger <kevenb@nwb.qc.ca>
1.07	16 March 2004, Simon Trimmer <simon@urbanmyth.org>
	updated the 1.06 tarball with newer microcode from Intel
